A math library for parsing and evaluating expressions in real, interval and
vector contexts. It also supports simplification and differentiation of
expressions.

name: Lexer
desc:
The lexer creates tokens (see TokenType and Token) from an input string.
The input string is expected to be in
infix notation form.
The lexer can convert an infix stream into a
postfix stream
(Reverse Polish Notation) for further processing by a ShuntingYardParser.

name: Lexer.new
desc: Creates a new lexer.

name: intBuffer
desc: Buffer for numbers

name: shuntingYard
desc:
Transforms the lexer's token stream into RPN using the Shunting-yard
algorithm. Returns a list of Token in RPN form. Throws an
ArgumentError if the list is empty.

name: tokenize
desc:
Tokenizes a given input string.
Returns a list of Token in infix notation.

name: tokenizeToRPN
desc:
This method invokes the createTokenStream methode to create an infix token
stream and then invokes the shunting yard method to transform this stream
into a RPN (reverse polish notation) token stream.

tree in Postfix order.

name: derive
desc: Derives this expression with respect to the given variable.

name: name
desc: The name of this variable.

name: toString
desc:
Returns a string version of this expression.
Subclasses should override this method. The output should be kept
compatible with the ExpressionParser.

name: VariableCollector
desc: An expression visitor that collects all variables in an expression.

name: evaluate
desc: Evaluate the given expression.

name: Vector
desc: A vector of arbitrary size.

name: Vector.new
desc: Creates a vector with the given element expressions.

name: accept
desc:
Accepts an ExpressionVisitor and visits all nodes of this expression
tree in Postfix order.

name: derive
desc: Derives this expression with respect to the given variable.

name: elements
desc: The elements of this vector.

name: getConstantValue
desc:
Returns the constant value of this literal.
Throws StateError if literal is not constant, check before usage with
isConstant().

name: isConstant
desc: Returns true, if this literal is a constant.

name: length
desc: The length of this vector.

name: operator []
desc: Convenience operator to access vector elements.

name: simplify
desc: Simplifies all elements of this vector.

name: VectorEvaluator
desc:
The vector evaluator can operate on mixed datatypes,
so is typed less strict. The underlying data types could
be Vector2, Vector3, Vector4 and double (scalars).

name: VectorEvaluator.new
desc: Create a new evaluator with the given context.
